title: Russia 3-Month Interbank Rate
description: Russia 3-Month Interbank Rate was at 10.39 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Russia averaged 14.44 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 227.70 percent in May of 1995 and a record low of 1.40 percent in May of 2003. In Russia, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Russia Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Russia
